│ `ExtractValueInst` and correctly finds the underlying vector or scalar component,          │
│ preventing the illegal `extractelement` operation on a struct.\n\n```cpp\n//               │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/Scalarizer.cpp:421\n\n  if (auto *EV =                          │
│ dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(V)) {\n    // To handle extractvalue, we recursively scalarize  │
│ the aggregate operand.\n    // We also need to adjust the lane number to be relative to    │
│ the aggregate.\n    // To do that, we add the size of all the elements that appear in      │
│ the\n    // aggregate before the extracted element.\n    unsigned NewLane = Lane;\n        │
│ Type *AggTy = EV->getAggregateOperand()->getType();\n    // FIXME: This only handles a     │
