│ implemented\");\n    for (unsigned I = 0, E = EV->getIndices()[0]; I < E; ++I) {\n         │
│ Type *ElTy = AggTy->getStructElementType(I);\n      NewLane +=                             │
│ DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ElTy);\n    }\n    V = EV->getAggregateOperand();\n    return         │
│ (*this)[NewLane];\n  }\n\n```\n\n### 5. Conclusion\n\nThe crash was caused by a flaw in    │
│ the `Scalarizer`'s `Scatterer` helper class, which did not account for `ExtractValueInst`  │
│ instructions. This led to an invalid attempt to treat a struct-typed value as a vector.    │
│ The proposed edit adds the necessary logic to handle `ExtractValueInst` correctly by       │
│ recursively descending into the aggregate structure, thereby resolving the crash."})       │
